it collection  including works by 19th century artist William D  Washington  are displayed in Preston Library  This page lists only those paintings located in the Library  Use your browser s  find  option to search for a subject  For detailed information about these and other paintings at VMI contact the VMI Museum  3rd Floor  Gallery   adjacent areas  primarily World Wars I   II  Almond  Edward   Class of 1915  Lt  Gen  USA Bucher  Oliver B   Class of 1917  VMI Commandant  1946 1951  BG USA Buckner  Simon B   Class of 1906  Lt  Gen  USA  Killed in action June 1945  Burress  Withers A   Class of 1914  MG USA Frazer  George Preston  Class of 1929  MAJ USA Gerow  Leonard T   Class of 1911  Gen  USA  Handy  George B J   Class of 1940  Lt  USA  1st VMI alumnus to die in WWII  Handy  Thomas T   Class of 1914  GEN USA  Hathaway  Edward T   Class of 1915  Lt  AEF WWI  Killed in France 1918  Lowry  Sumter   Class of 1914  Lt  Gen  USA Marshall  George C   Class of 1901  Gen  USA Patton  George S  Jr   Class of 1907  GEN USA  Pate  Randolph Mc Class of 1921  GEN USMC 4th Floor Gallery   Civil War portraits by William D  Washington  Related information Washington bio   online exhibit Allen  James W   Class of 1849  KIA Gaines s Mill  1862  Chenoweth  Joseph   Class of 1859  KIA 1862  Crutchfield  Stapleton  Class of 1855  KIA 1865  Garland  Samuel  Class of 1849  KIA 1862  Jackson  Stonewall  VMI Faculty CSA GEN  Latimer  Joseph W   Class of 1863  Mortally wounded at Gettysburg  Lee  Robert E  GEN CSA Marr  John Quincy  Class of 1846  KIA 1861 Otey  George Gaston  Class of 1855  Died from wounds received in battle  1862 Rodes  Robert E   Class of 1848  KIA 1864  Stuart  James E B  CSA Gen  Mortally wounded 1864  4th Floor  Archives Reading Room  M F  8 00 a m 4 30 p m  The Patton portraits were painted by William D  Washington  Gilham  William  Faculty  1846 1864  Patton  George S   Class of 1852  Mortally wounded at Winchester  1864  Patton  Waller Tazewell  Class of 1855  D